      <sec id="Sec4">
        <title>Dislocation breakpoints in the de-Bruijn graph</title>
        <p id="Par23">We consider the de-Bruijn graph over a set of circular input mitogenomes <italic>G</italic> as a directed multigraph. Its vertex set <italic>V</italic> comprises all <italic>k</italic>-mers in <italic>G</italic>, i.e., substrings of length <italic>k</italic> in <italic>G</italic>. These can be obtained by sliding a window of length <italic>k</italic> over the genome sequences. The edges are 4-tuples of the form <inline-formula id="IEq56"><alternatives><tex-math id="M111">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$(v,v',r,p)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M112"><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>v</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>v</mml:mi><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:msup><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>r</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>p</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5371_Article_IEq56.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and correspond to the substring <italic>s</italic> of length <inline-formula id="IEq57"><alternatives><tex-math id="M113">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$(k+1)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M114"><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5371_Article_IEq57.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> in genome <inline-formula id="IEq58"><alternatives><tex-math id="M115">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
