        <p id="Par70">The first experiment concerns closely related bony fish, <italic>Sillago aeolus</italic> and <italic>Sillago sinica</italic>. The two mitogenomes differ only by the exchanged position of two consecutive tRNA genes (cf. Additional file <xref rid="MOESM1" ref-type="media">1</xref>: Section <italic>Gene orders of dislocation case study 1</italic> and Additional file <xref rid="MOESM1" ref-type="media">1</xref>: Figure S11). This results in six putative breakpoints (cf. Table <xref rid="Tab3" ref-type="table">3</xref>). DeBBI successfully identified all of them with deviations of less than <inline-formula id="IEq440"><alternatives><tex-math id="M881">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
