				\begin{document}$$n_{\text{ra}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M924"><mml:msub><mml:mi>n</mml:mi><mml:mtext>ra</mml:mtext></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5371_Article_IEq461.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, i.e., the discrepancy in the gene orders. A large number of putative breakpoints results in a larger number of bulge candidates that need to be analyzed so that the runtimes are longer for larger values of <inline-formula id="IEq462"><alternatives><tex-math id="M925">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
