      <p id="Par46">Inversions are rearrangements that invert a continuous part of the chromosome. As a consequence, a sequence of genes, which was located on the affected segment on one strand, will be located on the opposite strand afterward. On the sequence level, this means that the corresponding encoding sequence <inline-formula id="IEq314"><alternatives><tex-math id="M627">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
