      <p id="Par62">Note that, in order to facilitate the computation of the precise breakpoint locations in the simulated data sets, only nucleotide substitutions are considered in the simulated sequences. The position of the gene boundaries is thus not altered before the gene blocks are rearranged/inverted in the sequences. Contrarily, if insertions and deletions had been incorporated additionally, these events might have affected the gene boundaries and consequently the breakpoint locations themselves.<fig id="Fig9"><label>Fig. 9</label><caption><p>Empirical distribution functions (EDFs) of the synthetic dislocation experiments. The four plots summarize the result quality for the experiments with one, three, five, and ten gene dislocations per genome and different substitution rates <inline-formula id="IEq412"><alternatives><tex-math id="M825">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
